    {
        "sha": "aa3012c49ee685d70b90c65ee6e2361d9826e565",
        "author": "datashaman",
        "email": "marlinf@datashaman.com",
        "date": "2024-02-15T12:37:13Z",
        "message": "Eliminate race condition with makeDirectory\n\nThis should not check whether the directory exists.\r\n\r\nWith parallel tests running in the same code area, you have a race condition between these two points:\r\n\r\n* does the directory exist\r\n* create the directory\r\n\r\nOne test sees the directory does not exist, and tries to create it. At the same time another test has created it.\r\nNow the first test fails because the directory now exists.\r\n\r\nTo fix this, you should not check anything and use the force option which this PR implements.",
        "url": "https://github.com/mewebstudio/Purifier/commit/aa3012c49ee685d70b90c65ee6e2361d9826e565"
    },
